5.2.k.
Infinite Play Programme Resell
Participation
PROCESSING
adidas
has partnered with our Selling Partner - Stuffstr Limited (“Stuffstr”) - to
provide consumers the opportunity to sell back eligible adidas products in
return for adidas gift cards through the adidas Infinite Play resell Programme
(“the Programme”).
For
the Programme, we will need to use the following information:
Contact Information – so Stuffstr knows where
to pick up your items, send you bags to pack your items, and to issue gift
cards to the right person, and you will receive adidas Gift Cards via email or
in-app messages;
Payment, Purchase and Transaction
Information – as gift cards are issued based on the length of the item
purchased, we need to verify when you actually bought the items; and
Membership Administration Information – you
get points when you resell your items according to adiClub Terms and
Conditions.
Stuffstr
will conclude the contract with you directly, so they can collect the items
from you, sell the products for recycling, and provide you with gift cards in
return. If you need more bags for the items you wish to resell, you will be
redirected to the Stuffstr website to provide additional information.
Profiling:
Stuffstr staff will be manually assessing the status of the items you resell
and create a profile for the items you have resold through the Programme.
Stuffstr uses this information to determine their future assessment for your
items. If you have consistently returned items that are more worn out than
expected (the original return price), Stuffstr may provide a different value
based on your profile.
Labels
Scanning: you have the option to use your device camera to scan the labels of
the adidas products you want to sell back to us. We will use the labels
pictures to recognize information about the product (size, materials, model,
production date) and to identify whether the product is genuine or not.
To
analyse the labels we use the Google Machine Learning Kit
(https://developers.google.com/ml-kit/vision/barcode-scanning). Your label
pictures will not be shared with Google.
We
will ask for your permission before you use your camera to try this feature.
